<p>
<strong>strlen</strong>
</p>

<p>
Syntax: 

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstring&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">size_t</span> <span class="kw3">strlen</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy2">*</span>str <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

Die Funktion strlen() gibt die Länge des in Klammern angegebenen Strings zurück. Das abschliessenden \0 wird nicht mitgezählt.
</p>

<p>
Zum Beispiel:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     <span class="kw3">printf</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Enter your name: &quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
     <span class="kw3">scanf</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;%s&quot;</span>, name <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
     <span class="kw3">printf</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Hello, your name has %d chars.<span class="es1">\n</span>&quot;</span>, <span class="kw3">strlen</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>name<span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
